  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SEACON - Shelter Support to Earthquake Affected Communities in Nepal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activities associated with this project include:

- Training needs assessment of masonry, carpentry and welding			
- Conducting cascading training on masonry, carpentry and welding for disaster resilient shelter construction methodologies		
- Training on masonry for local people on disaster resilient shelter structures and techniques.		
- Training on carpentry for local people on disaster resilient shelter structures and techniques.		
- Training on welding for local people on disaster resilient shelter structures and techniques.		
-Awareness Building on safe shelter methodologies for house owners, authorities and local key stakeholders</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall goal of the project is to provide security, safety, and protection, and build the resilience of earthquake affected and vulnerable households and communities.

The specific objective is to meet the basic recovery needs of earthquake affected and vulnerable households and communities to have access to adequate shelter and improved capacity in managing current and future disaster.</narrative>
  </description>
